License.

The Vita FPGA Architecture Verilog files VitaFPGAArchLogicBlock.v and
VitaFPGAArchMemoryBlock.v are bugfree.

Using two input, one output nand or two input, one output nor gates,
one can express any possible truth table.

The VitaFPGAArchMemoryBlock.v file implements a D-Flip Flop with two
configurable inputs and two configurable outputs that output the same
value in two directions.

The VitaFPGAArchLogicBlock.v file implements a LUT2 with two
configurable inputs and two outputs outputting one bit in two
directions.

A LUT2 can be programmed to ignore one or both inputs.

Thus, any possible truth table can be expressed with enough Vita FPGA
Architecture Logic Blocks. Thus, any integrated circuit can be
possible, given enough Vita FPGA Architecture Logic Blocks are used.

You are welcome to check out how it works, as explained by the
Documentation file and the source code files.

The Vita FPGA Architecture Synthesizer Subproject is under development,
and is licensed under The VitaSet License.
